<p>Right to be forgotten (RTBF) - sensitive data that is inadequate, irrelevant, no longer necessary to be kept in public domain&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>RTBF distinct than RTP. RTP - info not in public domain, but neds to be protected.&nbsp;</p>
<p>RTBF = in public domain but needs to be protected .&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>RTBF contradict RTI + FoSE.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>RTBF in India = no legal basis&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>Puttaswamy = RTP as FR , RTBF is in SYNC with RTP</li>
<li>BN srikrishna draft on PDP Bill = defines RTBF = ability of individual to edit, delete personal info on internet that is irrelevant&nbsp;
<ol>
<li>Consent to use data has been withdrawn (data principles ) section 27</li>
<li>DPA (data protection authority) =&nbsp; balance RTBF vs FoSE + RTI</li></ol></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Way forward</h3>
<ol>
<li>19(2) - privacy as RR on FoSE&nbsp;</li>
<li>Golden trinity = 14,19,21 = conflict developing among them.&nbsp;</li></ol>
